Q. Why we need to convert .py file to .exe file?
ANS. The simplest answer to this question is that it allows users without python in their software to use our python
software

Q2. How to covert .py files to .exe files?
ANS. Steps are:-

1. Install python module pyinstaller in your system(pip install pyinstller).Note that it should be installed in the same
directory in which your program is stored

2. Type pyinstaller.yourfilename in the command prompt\shell in the directory the code is stored.It may take some time
though.For creating a good software don't ignore warnings shown

NOTE:- If you want your .exe file in simple compressed form,type the given code in the command prompt:-
 pyinstaller --onefile yourfilename
 Also, note that the exe file immediateley closes once the task is finished


